---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { providerGroups } from "../facts";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Providers · Squeezy"
  description="Squeezy provider support across native APIs, OAuth subscription routes, local runtimes, and OpenAI-compatible services."
  active="providers"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">providers</span>
      <h1>Bring your model. Keep the optimization local.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Squeezy is multi-provider, but the cost-saving work happens before the
        provider call: local graph navigation, bounded tools, lazy schemas,
        compaction, routing, and session accounting.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">catalog shape</span>
      <h2>Native APIs, OAuth routes, local runtimes, and compatible endpoints.</h2>
      <p>
        Provider availability depends on your local config, credentials, and the
        selected model. Squeezy keeps unknown pricing honest: when registry
        metadata is missing, dollar estimates may be unavailable instead of
        invented.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="matrix">
      {
        providerGroups.map((row) => (
          <article class="matrix-row">
            <div><h3>{row.name}</h3></div>
            <p>{row.detail}</p>
            {row.status && <span class="status-pill">{row.status}</span>}
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section band">
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">routing</span>
        <h3>Cheap routing stays provider-local</h3>
        <p>When a narrow mechanical turn is eligible, Squeezy can use the configured provider's small-fast tier. It does not silently jump to a different provider.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">accounting</span>
        <h3>Usage is normalized, estimates are guarded</h3>
        <p>Provider streams normalize token and cache counters where available. USD estimates require pricing metadata for the selected provider/model pair.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">credentials</span>
        <h3>Keys and OAuth live locally</h3>
        <p>API keys, credential files, env vars, OAuth login flows, Bedrock credential chains, and local runtimes are configured on your machine.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">configuration example</span>
      <h2>Start with a provider, then tune routing and cost controls.</h2>
      <p>
        The exact model catalog changes over time. The provider registry and
        docs are the source for current presets, pricing metadata, cache
        capability, context estimates, and live-test status.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card code-card">
      <pre><code>[model]
provider = "openrouter"
model = "anthropic/claude-opus-4-7"

[providers.openrouter]
api_key_env = "OPENROUTER_API_KEY"

[router]
enabled = true</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p class="footnote">
      Live provider tests are intentionally gated by credentials, a costly-test
      feature, and an explicit opt-in environment variable.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
